{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"anesthetic-cerate-chick","description":"## What\nAdd `batch_stage_and_commit(tracker, items)` (and a batched `write_and_push` variant) to\n`src/rebar/_store/event_append.py`: commit MANY events under ONE write-lock acquire + ONE\n`git commit`, all-or-nothing. `items` is a sequence of `(ticket_id, event_dict)`.\n\n## Why\nThe single-event write path (`stage_and_commit`) commits one git graph per event (~3.3\ncommits/event). The write lock (`_store/lock.py`) is NOT re-entrant, so a caller cannot\nloop `stage_and_commit` under one lock. A dedicated batch primitive is the seam bulk\ncallers (the importer, B2) use to collapse N commits into 1. Batching is invariant-safe\nbecause replay/dedup/union-merge/SNAPSHOT-compaction key off each event's per-event UUID,\nnot commit boundaries (each event stays its own I2 uuid-named file).\n\n## Scope\n- `src/rebar/_store/event_append.py` only. Single-event `stage_and_commit`/`write_and_push`\n  behavior unchanged (the reversibility guarantee).\n- Validate + canonical-stage every event BEFORE taking the lock; then under ONE lock:\n  atomic-rename each temp into `{ticket}/{ts}-{uuid}-{TYPE}.json`, one `git add`, ONE\n  `git commit`.\n- All-or-nothing rollback: any failure (validation, rename, add, non-recoverable commit)\n  unstages AND unlinks ALL already-placed paths, not just the failing one.\n- Generalize `_recover_from_unmerged` to re-add the FULL batch path list on retry.\n- Empty batch = no-op (no lock, no commit).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `batch_stage_and_commit(tracker, items)` in `src/rebar/_store/event_append.py`: one lock acquire, N I2 uuid-named files, exactly one commit; returns the event count\n- [ ] `batch_write_and_push` variant: batch commit then ONE best-effort push\n- [ ] All-or-nothing rollback on validation / rename / `git add` / non-recoverable `git commit` failure: every already-renamed path unstaged from the index AND unlinked from disk\n- [ ] `_recover_from_unmerged` (bug 6818 UU self-heal) re-adds the full batch path list on retry — a batched commit self-heals a pre-existing unmerged `.bridge_state/*`\n- [ ] Empty batch is a no-op (no lock taken, no commit made)\n- [ ] Single-event `stage_and_commit`/`write_and_push` path unchanged; existing regression tests (`tests/unit/test_store_write_index_reset_on_failure.py`, `tests/unit/test_store_write_unmerged_recovery.py`) stay green\n- [ ] New unit tests in `tests/unit/test_store_batch_write.py` cover: N-in-one-commit, canonical-byte parity vs single path, empty no-op, validation/commit rollback, next-write-uncontaminated, UU self-heal\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` all green","id":"890d-4733-1c88-4976","parent_id":"ce4c-f963-363b-44b6","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"B1: batch_stage_and_commit — batched-commit write primitive in _store"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783649383103209001,"uuid":"0dfda219-e747-4ee8-ad39-eac8dde2b779"}